node.text: Just a few hours before the @paralympics Closing Ceremony we catch up with @birgitskarstein - a para-athlete from Norway 🇳🇴 . She competed at Sochi, Rio, PyeongChang, and now at the Tokyo 2020 Paralympic Games, where she won a gold medal. Birgit tells us why the Paralympics are so important and how she is spending her time after the Games.

node.text:
A letter from double Olympic champion, Mariana Pajon, to her grandmother. ❤️⁠
⁠
"Tita Rosita, I know you are there. I am sure of it. Although, because of your years and so many things you have lived and overcome, you hardly recognise me now. And even more because of my absence this year, as I am fighting for another great dream. I know that sparks of joy come to you when I return to see you, when you touch me, just as I feel it when I hold your hand and give you a hug.⁠
⁠
I know that although you do not remember much, that your granddaughter, who rides a bike around the world, promised to bring you another medal to hang on to you, so that you could touch it and feel it in your hands again. And when I saw your smile and how you looked at me, I am sure that your heart is proud which makes me the happiest granddaughter to see you laugh. ⁠
⁠
You have taught me all this. To get up, to fight to get ahead when we have lost everything, to never give up on our dreams, no matter how trampled we are, and to always keep believing, even when we think that life has taken everything from us as it happened to you. But here you are, still with us and leaving us a more valuable legacy than any medal. Thanks, Tita!⁠
⁠
Mission accomplished bringing you back to the "here and now", at least for a few seconds to make you happy."⁠
⁠
